<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,1358,1925]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Morphology. D VI + I,8–9; A I,7–9; P 15–17 (summarized in 
<bibRefCitation author="Kovtun, O. A. &amp; Manilo, L. G." box="[886,1154,1395,1421]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="307 - 314" refId="ref59524" refString="Kovtun, O. A. &amp; Manilo, L. G. (2013) Mediterranean fish - Gammogobius steinitzi Bath, 1971 (Actinopterygii: Perciformes: Gobiidae) - a new representative of the Black Sea ichthyofauna. Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 43, 307 - 314. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIP 2013.43.4.08" type="journal article" year="2013">
Kovtun &amp; 
<collectingRegion box="[1005,1086,1395,1421]" country="Philippines" name="Manila" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Manilo</collectingRegion>
2013
</bibRefCitation>
). Small goby with stocky body, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[221,804,1430,1457]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">large depressed head and a gently sloping snout</emphasis>
. Eyes large, with a narrow interorbital space (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1424,1431,1457]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="24.[151,250,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,1146,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-43@24.[173,1414,1146,1976]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 22. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gammogobius steinitzi Bath, 1971. Photo by S. Guerrieri, Tuscany, Italy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601635/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Caudal peduncle deep, almost as deep as the body. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin with more or less rounded shape and no elongated spines, all but the sixth spines being subequal in length. Caudal fin rounded. Scales visible on body from reticulate pigmentation pattern along scale edges.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,1358,1925]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Live coloration. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Body with barred coloration pattern of 6–7 narrow pale bars on a mostly brownish background</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[311,395,1611,1637]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="24.[151,250,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,1146,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-43@24.[173,1414,1146,1976]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 22. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gammogobius steinitzi Bath, 1971. Photo by S. Guerrieri, Tuscany, Italy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601635/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
). Head brownish with 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">3 pale, continuous bars extending downwards from eye over cheek and preopercle to ventral side</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[516,614,1647,1674]" captionStart="FIGURE 20" captionStartId="23.[151,250,1888,1912]" captionTargetBox="[154,1434,1212,1864]" captionTargetId="figure-41@23.[154,1434,1212,1864]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 20. Three pale, uninterrupted bars (marked with numbers) extending downwards from eye radiating downwards from eye to ventral side: A) C. liechtensteini, B) G. steinitzi. Photos by M. Kovačić (fishes photographed in a tank)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601629" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601629/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 20b</figureCitation>
). Fins mostly colorless; some 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">black spots at the base of both dorsal fins, extending as dots along rays or spine</emphasis>
s (
<figureCitation box="[616,700,1683,1709]" captionStart="FIGURE 22" captionStartId="24.[151,250,2000,2024]" captionTargetBox="[173,1414,1146,1976]" captionTargetId="figure-43@24.[173,1414,1146,1976]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 22. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Gammogobius steinitzi Bath, 1971. Photo by S. Guerrieri, Tuscany, Italy." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601635" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601635/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,1358,1925]" box="[199,979,1719,1745]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Benthic" baseAuthorityName="Kolombatovic" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[383,705,1719,1745]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Corcyrogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="liechtensteini">
<emphasis box="[383,705,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Corcyrogobius liechtensteini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ahnelt &amp; Patzner" authorityYear="1995" box="[720,972,1719,1745]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Didogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="splechtnai">
<emphasis box="[720,972,1719,1745]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Didogobius splechtnai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,1358,1925]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Habitat. Infralittoral species, known from 
<quantity box="[688,776,1754,1781]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" unit="m" value="15.0" valueMax="25.0" valueMin="5.0">5–25 m</quantity>
in marine caves, more common in deeper water. Mostly inhabits the crevices and holes of cave walls and ceilings (summarized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Patzner, R. A." box="[985,1136,1791,1817]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref62855" refString="Patzner, R. A. (2021) Gobiidae. Available from: http: // www. patzner. sbg. ac. at / Gobiidae / GobiidaeSpecies. htm (accessed 1 October 2021)" type="url" year="2021">Patzner 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1437,1358,1925]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
Geographic distribution. Mediterranean and Black Sea. Mediterranean records from the northwestern Mediterranean (
<bibRefCitation author="Bath, H." box="[332,455,1863,1889]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="201 - 210" refId="ref51460" refString="Bath, H. (1971) Gammogobius steinitzi n. gen. n. sp. aus dem westlichen Mittelmeer. Senckenbergiana Biologica, 52, 201 - 210." type="journal article" year="1971">Bath 1971</bibRefCitation>
), Adriatic Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Kovacic, M." box="[637,802,1863,1889]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 7" refId="ref57675" refString="Kovacic, M. (1999) Gammogobius steinitzi Bath, 1971, a fish new to the Adriatic Sea. Natura Croatica, 8 (1), 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1999">Kovačić 1999</bibRefCitation>
), Crete (Kovačić 
<emphasis box="[1007,1059,1863,1889]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al</emphasis>
. 2011), and 
<collectingCountry box="[1207,1288,1863,1889]" name="Turkey" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, Aegean Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Engin, S. &amp; Irmak, E. &amp; Seyhan, D. &amp; Akdemir, T. &amp; Keskin, A. C." box="[159,370,1899,1925]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="1073 - 1084" refId="ref54133" refString="Engin, S., Irmak, E., Seyhan, D., Akdemir, T. &amp; Keskin, A. C. (2018 a) Gobiid fishes of the coastal zone of the Northeastern Aegean Sea. Marine Biodiversity, 48, 1073 - 1084. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12526 - 016 - 0550 - x" type="journal article" year="2018">
Engin 
<emphasis box="[234,284,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al</emphasis>
. 2018a
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ragkousis, M. &amp; Digenis, M. &amp; Kovacic, M. &amp; Katsanevakis, S. &amp; Gerovasileiou, V." box="[381,627,1899,1925]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="557" refId="ref63299" refString="Ragkousis, M., Digenis, M., Kovacic, M., Katsanevakis, S. &amp; Gerovasileiou, V. (2021) Rarely reported cryptobenthic fish in marine caves of the Eastern Mediterranean Sea. Journal of Marine Science and Engeneering, 9, 557. https: // doi. org / 10.3390 / jmse 9060557" type="journal article" year="2021">
Ragkousis 
<emphasis box="[504,553,1899,1925]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
). In the Black Sea, it was recorded in Crimea (
<bibRefCitation author="Kovtun, O. A. &amp; Manilo, L. G." box="[1149,1419,1899,1925]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="307 - 314" refId="ref59524" refString="Kovtun, O. A. &amp; Manilo, L. G. (2013) Mediterranean fish - Gammogobius steinitzi Bath, 1971 (Actinopterygii: Perciformes: Gobiidae) - a new representative of the Black Sea ichthyofauna. Acta Ichthyologica et Piscatoria, 43, 307 - 314. https: // doi. org / 10.3750 / AIP 2013.43.4.08" type="journal article" year="2013">Kovtun &amp; Manilo 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
